## 🐛 Bug Report

Type definition has no `forEachAddress` function definition.

https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/2ab468b8bae2c8d5844f922d61ac7d960fee26be/index.d.ts#L927-L972

https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/2ab468b8bae2c8d5844f922d61ac7d960fee26be/lib/doc/range.js#L248-L254

Lib version: 4.2.1

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```ts
  const style = {numFmt:'### ### ### ###'};
  const range = new Range('B5','C99');

  // There is no `forEachAddress` in a index.d.ts
  range.forEachAddress((address) => {worksheet.getCell(address).style = {...style} });
```

## The expected behavior:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->
No error

## Current workaround

By adding `@ts-ignore`

```ts
  const style = {numFmt:'### ### ### ###'};

  const range = new Range('B5','C99');

  // There is no `forEachAddress` in a index.d.ts
  // @ts-ignore 
  range.forEachAddress((address) => {worksheet.getCell(address).style = {...style} });
```
